HEADWORD: Aperient
<hw>A*pe"ri*ent</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aperiens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>aperire</ets> to uncover, open;
<ets>ab</ets> + <ets>parire</ets>, <ets>parere</ets>, to bring forth,
produce. Cf. <er>Cover</er>, <er>Overt</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Gently opening the bowels; laxative.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>An aperient medicine or food.</def></def2>
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aperitive</ent>⟦br⟧
